Spring Boot MVC - Day 3 Tasks (Model & Map)
Topic
Passing Hardcoded Data from Controller to JSP
Rules
Use Spring Boot MVC.
Use JSP only.
Do not use JSTL.
Add hardcoded data in the controller.
Display data using Expression Language (EL) (${...}).
Task 1: Using Model (Single Student Details)
Objective: Pass hardcoded student details from the controller to the JSP using Model.
URL: http://localhost:8080/student
Controller Data:
Student Name : Rahul
Course : Java Full Stack
City : Hyderabad
Use:
model.addAttribute("name","Rahul");
model.addAttribute("course","Java Full Stack");
model.addAttribute("city","Hyderabad");
JSP Output:
Student Details
Student Name : Rahul
Course : Java Full Stack
City : Hyderabad
Display using:
${name}
${course}
${city}
No JSTL